item.title: Rsps 317 jarring
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

[quote=“Mikeyzzz, post:3, topic:546039”][quote author=wetodded link=topic=664930.msg4449210#msg4449210 date=1410389318]
Why are you jarring the client?
[/quote]Webclient I assume.[/quote]
Or… You know, to compress the class files into a single .jar that can be executed without needing any special program (like an IDE) or a script (like a .bat or .sh)… You can also use tools to obfuscate the class files after jaring, to add better security to your code…

OP:
If it can’t find the main class, make sure you set the manifest correctly in your jaring tool (like jarmaker). Typically, a 317 client’s main class is ‘client’. no quotes.
